 How to Connect to your HANA server on AWS 
 
 
 
 
 
Log on to Amazon EC2 and start your SAP HANA instance. In the “Navigation” frame, navigate to “INSTANCES&gt;Instances”. This should show all your instances  in Amazon EC2. Make sure the HANA instance you want to connect  to is in “running” state. If not, choose the instance, then click on “Instance Actions” menu, and click on “Start” in the pull down menu. 
Associate your Elastic IP with SA